{{zh-hanzi|[[多]][[多]][[益]][[善]]}}
==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: duō duō yì shàn
===Etymology===
From the "The Biography of the [[Marquess]] of [[w:Hán Xìn|Huai Yin]]" in the ''[[w:Records of the Grand Historian|Records of the Grand Historian]]''
#: [[劉邦|上]][[常]][[從容]][[與]][[韓信|信]][[言]][[諸]][[將]][[能]][[不]]，[[各]][[有]][[差]]。[[劉邦|上]][[問]][[曰]]：「[[如]][[我]][[能]][[將]][[幾何]]？」[[韓信|信]][[曰]]：「[[陛下]][[不]][[過]][[能]][[將]][[十]][[萬]]。」[[劉邦|上]][[曰]]：「[[於]][[君]][[何如]]？」[[曰]]：「[[臣]]'''多多而益善'''[[耳]]。」
#: ''[[w:Liu Bang|His majesty]] chatted with [[w:Hán Xìn|Han Xin]] about the capabilities of the generals.  Each had their shortcomings.  [[w:Liu Bang|His majesty]] asked, "How many troops could I lead?"  [[w:Hán Xìn|Han Xin]] replied, "Your highness should not lead more than 10,000."  [[w:Liu Bang|His majesty]] said, "And what about you?"  "For your humble servant, '''the more the merrier'''!" said [[w:Hán Xìn|Han Xin]].''
*This quote lead to the famous saying:
{|border=1 cellspacing="0"
|- valign="center"
| bgcolor="#dfefff"|
'''[[Simplified Chinese]]'''
|[[韩信点兵，多多益善]]
|- valign="center"
| bgcolor="#dfefff"|
'''[[Traditional Chinese]]'''
|[[韓信點兵，多多益善]]
|}
([[w:Hán Xìn|Han Xin]] counts his troops, '''the more the merrier''')

===Proverb===
# [[the more the merrier]].

